# Tailwind UI Rules

## Theme

Use brand tokens from `globals.css` (`brand-*`, `surface`, `muted`) instead of arbitrary hex values.

## Components

Always prefer shared UI primitives:

- `Button` — variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `danger`
- `Input`, `Label`, `Textarea` — form fields
- `Card` — content containers
- `Badge`, `Alert`, `Tabs` — status and navigation
- `PageHeader`, `EmptyState` — page scaffolding

## Layout

- Mobile-first: stack on small screens, grid/sidebar on `md:` and up
- Customer flows must remain readable on phone and desktop
- Use consistent spacing: `gap-4`, `p-4`, `p-6` for sections

## Avoid

- One-off inline styles for buttons or inputs
- Hard-coded colors outside the theme
- Dark-mode-only layouts (light warm coffee shop aesthetic)
